<HEADLINE> Australian Swimmer Kicked Out of Sports Institute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Swimmer Scott Miller, Olympic
silver medalist, was kicked out of the Australian Institute of
Sports (AIS) for his failure to meet the training commitment, AIS
director said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
John Boultbee said he had informed Miller of the decision after
consultation with head coach Don Talbot and ordered Miller to pack
up his belongs because "this isn't the place for you."
</P>
<P>
Miller who won the 100-meter butterfly silver medal in Atlanta,
had missed many of the sessions at the team camp in Canberra last
week.
</P>
<P>
Miller explained that he had informed the AIS that his
sponsorship commitments would take up some of his time and he
would not participate in a full training program because of an
injury to his shoulder.
</P>
<P>
However, Australian swimming officials said Miller was still in
the Australian team for the Pan Pacific championships in Fukuoka,
Japan, from August 12-15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
