<HEADLINE> 8 People Missing in Oil Tanker Explosion in East China Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- An explosion on an oil tanker at
the Qixia Anchorage in Nanjing, Jiangsu Province, this afternoon
caused the ship and a barge to sink and set two other barges on
fire.
</P>
<P>
Eight sailors were reported missing in the explosion, which
took place at 14:44, while the tanker was unloading oil onto the
barges, according to the Ministry of Communications.
</P>
<P>
The tanker, "Daqing 243", belongs to the Guangzhou Ocean
Shipping Group.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities sent rescue teams to the site immediately
after the explosion and the fire was brought under control and
measures were being taken to prevent the oil from polluting the
nearby water.
</P>
<P>
The ministry is investigating the cause of the accident.
</P>
</TEXT>
