<HEADLINE> Bombay Sensitive Index Gains 22.57 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market today gained 22.57 points to close
3861.42 as against Tuesday's close of 3838.85.
</P>
<P>
The national index also moved up further by 11.22 points to
1656.06 from 1644.84 previously.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the US dollar index were quoted up at 369.17
and 171.78 compared with overnight close of 367.06 and 170.66.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said that Tata Tea attracted fresh buying support in
view of continued rumors of take-over of the company by hind
lever. Associated Cement Company scored further impressive gains
on sustained interested buying ahead of the company's board
meeting on June 18 to approve finalization of accounts for the
year 1996-97.
</P>
<P>
MTNL, Telco and Tata Chem dropped moderately on local selling
pressure.  
</P>
