<HEADLINE> Gontchar Wins Stage, Gotti Retains Overall Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Serguei Gontchar sprinted ahead to
take the 18th stage in Cavalese on Wednesday, but Ivan Gotti
retained his overall lead in the Tour of Italy cycling race.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's Gontchar completed the 40 kilometers course from
Baselga di Pine to Cavalese in 47 minutes and 18 seconds by
averaging 50 kph.
</P>
<P>
Gotti, trying to become the first Italian in six years to win
the Giro, was only 14 seconds behind Tonkov.
</P>
<P>
Now, Gotti held the edge of 37 seconds into Thursday's leg, a
222-kilometer route through the Dolemites that includes several
tough climbs.
</P>
<P>
The tour will end on June 8 in Milan. 
</P>
