<HEADLINE> Iran Blanks Kirghizstan in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Iran blanked Kirghizstan 7-0 in
its second game in Group two of the Asian World Cup qualifying
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Bagheri Karim scored the opener in the 36th minute to help Iran
enter the second half on 1-0.
</P>
<P>
All the other goals were packed in the second half as the
Iranians enjoyed physical superiority over their peers.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Iran set a World Cup record by beating the Maldives
17-0.
</P>
<P>
Syria was awarded three points by the soccer's world governing
body as Kirghizstan failed to show up for its scheduled meet on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Iran led the group with six points from two straight
wins, and is tipped to advance to the second round of ten teams to
vie for three or four berths for the 1998 World Cup finals in
France. 
</P>
