<DOCNO> XIE19970605.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Korea, Kyrgyzstan to Promote Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 4 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim Young-sam
and visiting Kyrgyz President Askar Akayev held a summit meeting
today and signed a joint declaration to enhance friendship and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The declaration calls for the two countries to promote mutual
investment and establish joint ventures and financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
Akayev, the first Kyrgyz president to visit South Korea since
the two countries established diplomatic relations in 1992,
arrived here Tuesday on a three-day visit.
</P>
<P>
Holding talks with Kim before the signing of the declaration,
Akayev called on South Korean businessmen to invest in Kyrgyzstan.
</P>
<P>
In turn, Kim asked for the Kyrgyz government's support in
helping Korean firms invest in Kyrgyzstan.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume between South Korea and Kyrgyzstan stood at 6.07
billion U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents agreed that South Korea will set up an
economic development cooperation fund for Kyrgyzstan to develop a
telecommunications modernization project and train people in
scientific and technological fields.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also agreed to set up a panel of business
executives to promote cooperation between the two countries'
private sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
