<HEADLINE> Zambia's Water Sector Not To Be Wholly Privatized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government will not wholly
privatize the water sector but instead enter into
partnership with the private sector, a government official has said.
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia today quoted Energy and Water Development Deputy
Permanent Secretary Sylvester Hibajene as saying here on Tuesday that
the government has realized that 100 percent privatization is not the
ideal solution for Zambia.
</P>
<P>
But he said that water supply and sanitation utilities will run on
a commercial basis to achieve financial and managerial autonomy.
</P>
<P>
He said that majority share holding will be in the public sector,
the water sector reforms seek to create an environment to encourage
partnerships with the private sector.
</P>
<P>
The government is working on a legal framework for contractual
arrangement with local authorities in providing water services, said
the official. 
