<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain to Lead Fight Against Global Warming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 4 (Xinhua) -- British Environment Minister Michael
Meacher said today his government will take a tough position and
lead the fight against global warming.
</P>
<P>
"We will take the hard decisions necessary to put the UK truly
at the forefront in tackling climate change. This government will
take the lead in the fight against global warming," Meacher said
at a conference on the climate crisis organized by the World Wide
Fund for Nature (WWF).
</P>
<P>
A world summit on environment and global warming will be held
in the Japanese city of Kyoto in December to agree on targets for
cutting emissions of greenhouse gases such as carbon dioxide which
warm the atmosphere and are widely blamed for changing the
climate.
</P>
<P>
The WWF says climate change is a greatest threat to species and
habitats worldwide and is urging governments to reduce emissions
of greenhouse gases by 20 percent by 2005.
</P>
<P>
The European Union has agreed in principle to a cut of 15
percent by 2010 but has so far enacted measures that would only
bring about a 10 percent cut.
</P>
<P>
Meacher pledged his government was pushing for a 20 percent
reduction by 2010 but would not blaze a trail if others refused to
follow.
</P>
<P>
"We are not in the business of picking up the tab for everyone
else and we are not offering more for others to do less," Meacher
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
