<HEADLINE> VAT Compliance Increased in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
lUSAKA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia Revenue Authority (ZRA) has
recorded an increase in Vvalue Added Tax (VAT) compliance following the
introduction of a 0.5 percent penalty for delayed payments.
</P>
<P>
ZRA Public Relations ,Manager Michael Mwape, who confirmed the
increase in compliance for April, said it is not easy to give the
specific number of companies that have been penalized because ZRA is
still monitoring the new penalty, according to the Zambia Daily Mail.
</P>
<P>
The penalty introduced on April 1 this year is charged on those
companies that make their VAT return submissions on time but without
making the payment.
</P>
<P>
Mwape said that to encourage compliance, the penalty is charged
everday that payment is overdue.
</P>
<P>
With this new penalty, there have been a significant reduction in
unaccompanied submissions, said Mwape. 
</P>
