<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, London Down Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Europe's major stock markets showed
gains today, but London slipped into the minus column as Wall
Street made a weak start.
</P>
<P>
British shares ended a choppy session mixed amid continued
uncertainty about possible interest rate hikes. Fears that rates
could be tightened by both the U.S. and British central banks in
the near term kept many participants out of the market. The
FTSE-100 index closed 0.7 of a point lower to 4,557.1.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German shares ended low-volume bourse trade 1
percent higher. The market lacked impetus to forge more
significant gains and continued to track late gains in electronic
trade from Tuesday. The DAX index closed at 3,661.84, up 36.10
points.
</P>
<P>
The Paris bourse finished in positive ground for the third
straight session this week since the Socialists came to power. The
market was enjoying a honeymoon period with the left and bargain
hunting helped support prices. The CAC-40 index closed up 10.88
points to 2,635.37. 
</P>
