<HEADLINE> 4 Workers Killed in Tanker Fire in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Four workers today were killed and
another injured in a powerful explosion in a tanker in Istanbul,
the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported this evening.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the blast, which occurred at 14:55
local time (11:55 GMT), caused fire in an empty 75,366-tonne
tanker named "Gole" for repair in Tuzla Tersaneler of Istanbul,
the largest city of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The injured worker was sent to a nearby hospital for
treatment, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
It added that other workers in the tanker had been transferred
to the place of security in the region.
</P>
<P>
However, the agency did not report the reason why the blast
occurred in the tanker.
</P>
<P>
On February 13, at least 20 fire fighters got injured when
extinguishing a fire caused by the explosion in an empty
307-meter-long petrol tanker in the same area of Istanbul.
</P>
