<HEADLINE> Macro-Economic Model Set Up in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has set up a
macro-economic model to track the effects of adjustment policies
on the economy in the medium- to long-term time-frame, a
government official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Benjamin Mweene, Secretary to the Treasury in the Ministry of
Finance and Economic Planning, said the model will show medium
and long term effects of policies like the structural adjustment
program.
</P>
<P>
He said that although the structural adjustment program has
been going on for some time, emphasis has been placed only on the
immediate consequences of the program.
</P>
<P>
The computable model will also be used to follow the evolution
of the economy in response to policy changes and thus lead to an
improvement in the country's economic management process, said
Mweene.
</P>
<P>
Mweene noted that the model will enrich policy debate and
contribute to a much wider search for options in the
implementation of the economic program of the country. 
</P>
