He said that although the maternal mortality ratio is
currently estimated at 730 per 100,000 live births compared to
940 per 100,000 in 1990, the figure is still among the highest in
the region.
</P>
<P>
When launching the family planning in reproductive health
policy framework document at a workshop held here, he said that
the launching of the policy document has come at the right time
when the health of mothers and children is at crossroad.
</P>
<P>
Kalumba said for a long time, the family planning service
providers in the country have no guidelines to enable them to
provide quality family planning information and services.
</P>
<P>
He assured health personnel of his ministry's continued
reviewing of existing legislation to ensure that they are not at
risk in implementing the family planning strategies and standards
contained in the document.
</P>
<P>
