<HEADLINE> Russia Proud of Border Agreement with Asian Neighbors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Russia's border agreement with its
Asian neighbors has created a model to solve border disputes,
Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Conference on Disarmament, which was held here
today, Primakov said the agreement on mutual reduction of military
forces in border areas signed between Russia and its Asian
neighbors China, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan was a
"serious achievement."
</P>
<P>
The agreement, signed by presidents of the five nations in
Moscow on April 24, set ceilings for ground forces, combat
and defensive aircraft within a 100-kilometer wide zone on both
sides of these borders.
</P>
<P>
"The value of this agreement lies not only in the fact that it
covers a truly large border-line. It creates a model for the
solution to border issues that are often very painful in the Asia
Pacific region," Primakov said. 
