<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Youth to Present Large Bronze Vessel To Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Some Hong Kong young people will
present a Bronze vessel to the motherland on June 21, to greet the
return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
It is modeled after "Simuwu", an ancient square cooking
vessel with two loop handles and four legs made during the Shang
Dynasty (1600 -- 1100 B.C.) for sacrificial offerings.
</P>
<P>
The 1,997-kg vessel is 2.22 meters high, 2 meters long, and 1.5
meters wide, and has a dragon and phoenix pattern and the emblem
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region on its sides.
</P>
<P>
The Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Youth League,
the All-China Youth Federation, and other units will organize a
celebration for the return of Hong Kong to the motherland on June
21 at Yuanming Yuan Park in north suburban Beijing, where
representatives of Hong Kong's young people will present the
vessel. The "Shenghe Baoding" (prosperous, harmonious, precious
vessel) is intended to wish eternal prosperity and harmony to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The event will make the park a place of patriotic lessons for
China's young people, said Liu Peng, chairman of the All-China
Youth Federation, at a news briefing in Beijing today. He said
that young people should be taught that "A poor and weak nation is
the target of invasion" and China can achieve its reunification
and make social progress only by "becoming prosperous and strong."
</P>
<P>
Yuanming Yuan was the imperial garden of the Qing Dynasty and
was destroyed by British and French troops in 1860.
</P>
<P>
About 1,000 representatives from Hong Kong and 56 ethnic groups
of China will attend the activity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
