<HEADLINE> Hingis Downs Seles to Reach French Open Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The 16-year-old Martina Hingis
reached her first French Open final here on Thursday by beating
three-time champion Monica Seles from one set down.
</P>
<P>
The top-ranked Swiss kept her unbeaten slate clean of the year
by downing Seles 6-7 (2-7), 7-5 and 6-4 to secure her outing to
the finals at Roland Garros.
</P>
<P>
Hingis was sure on course for her second straight Grand Slam
title after her victory at the Australian Open at the start of the
season.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will vie for the title against either Iva Majoli of
Croatia or Amanda Coetzer of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
In the first set, both Hingis and Seles had two breaks apiece
before being deadlocked 4-4 and Seles rushed to a 6-1 lead in the
tiebreaker which she eventually won as Hingis committed five
unforced errors.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of the second, Seles double-faulted at break
point, levelled after the fourth game, but dropped her serve again
in the very next.
</P>
<P>
Down 5-3, Seles survived two set points and broke anew at 5-5,
but made errors in a hurry to surrender her 11th game before
Hingis serveing out the set at love.
</P>
<P>
The key point in the third set came in the third game. After
Seles saved two break points, Hingis hit an angled forehand winner
for another break point before Seles dropped her serve by hitting
long. 
</P>
</TEXT>
