<HEADLINE> Heroin, Opium Destroyed In Southern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen in Guangdong Province,
the city and economic zone bordering on to Hong Kong, burned more
than 80 kilos of heroin, opium, "ice", and other drugs in front of
tens of thousands of people today.
</P>
<P>
From April 1 to June 2 of this year, Shenzhen, which was
China's pioneer in its reforms and opening to the outside world,
arrested 660 people suspected of drug dealing in 366 cases
involving drugs.
</P>
<P>
It also smashed 107 drug trafficking groups, confiscating 35
guns, 304 cartridges, and various knives in the process.
</P>
