<HEADLINE> Greater Economic Cooperation Between China And APEC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China is offering a wide range of
economic cooperation projects to the 17 other members of
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation organization, says Wang Dehe,
director of the organizing committee for the APEC Exposition in
Yantai, a port city in Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Wang says that China has different forms for promoting economic
cooperation with other APEC members: importing advanced technology
from advanced member countries, developing processing trade with
developing countries, and investing in the group of
under-developed member states.
</P>
<P>
The 31 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions have
prepared a number of economic projects for the exposition. Yantai
alone has proposed projects with a total investment of three
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Currently, about 80 percent of China's foreign trade is done
with APEC members and 90 percent of China's foreign investment
comes from APEC members.  
</P>
