<DOCNO> XIE19970605.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank Funds Banned From Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBC),
the central bank, today issued a circular prohibiting banks from
using funds for the stock market in any way.
</P>
<P>
The central bank ordered all commercial banks to halt all
involvement in trusts, investments, and stock businesses within
ten days.
</P>
<P>
Inter-bank borrowing and lending for trust and investment
companies, security dealers, and other non-banking institutions
must come under the strict supervision of PBC branches, the
circular says.
</P>
<P>
Overdrafts for stock trading are strictly prohibited and
enterprises may not use bank loans to sell or buy shares.
</P>
<P>
Commercial bank executives will be removed from their posts if
their banks are found to be involved in stock trading in direct or
indirect ways, within ten days from today, the circular says.
</P>
<P>
In related news, starting October 1, securities dealers found
manipulating stock trading will be dealt with in accordance with
the revised Criminal Law, it says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
