<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 12.43 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market today gained 12.43 points to 3863.38
as against the previous close of 3861.42.
</P>
<P>
The national index improved by 4.14 points to 1660.2 from
1656.06 yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar indexes were quoted up at 370.02
and 172.78 respectively compared with 369.17 and 171.78 yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Select shares advanced further as financial institutions and
speculators squared up their positions on the BSE market today but
the early gains were trimmed on profit taking at higher levels.
</P>
<P>
Reflecting the market activity, the BSE Sensitive Index opened
better at 3863.38, touched a high of 3901.45 during the early
session but profit taking at higher levels reduced the gains to
3873.85 at the close.
</P>
<P>
The market has staged a comeback with the Sensitive Index
gaining by more than 118 points during the week. Brokers are
optimistic that the market will continue to remain in the bull
orbit next week on firm support from investors.  
</P>
