<HEADLINE> Eight People Killed in Fighting Between Aidid's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 5 (xinhua)--At least eight people were killed
and nine others wounded yesterday when Somali militiamen at the
airport and others who were sent to fetch the newly printed money
fought over who would escort the money on its way to capital
Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
A package of newly printed Somali Shillings consignment worth
of US $ 750,000 is just an introductory part of nearly US $12
million which has allegedly been printed in malaysia. The arrival
of this money which has been brought by a plane led to the armed
confrontation at the airport within the supporters of Hussein
Mohamed Aidid.
</P>
<P>
According to Aidid's security officials today, security of the
airport has been restored back to normal. Commander of the
airport, Mukhtar Sayid Ahmed told joumalists that the differences
have now been settleed and the airport is officially open for
both the local and international flights.
</P>
<P>
There's no word yet from the government of Hussein Mohamed
Aidid over yesterday's incident nor the arrival of the money.
However, the one thousand Somali Shilling notes of the newly
arrived money have been seen in the main business center of
Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Other two Somalia's main factions have condemned the arrival
of the newly printed money. The factions led by Ali Mahdi Mohamed
and Osman Hassan Ali Atto today issued a joint communique,
condemning the country that printed the new consignment of money.
</P>
<P>
The two factions called on the United Nations, the
Organization of African Unity, the European Union and the Arab
League to take the necessary measures against the newly printed
money which they characterized as " fake".


