<HEADLINE> New Slovak FM Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia got its first female
foreign minister Wednesday after President Michal Kovac appointed
39-year-old Zdenka Kramplova to the post.
</P>
<P>
Kramplova studied agriculture in Bulgaria. When she returned,
she became an advisor to Slovak Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar and
then director of the prime minister's office and foreign
ministry's office.
</P>
<P>
Former Slovak foreign minister Pavol Hamzik resigned on May 26
when a nationwide referendum on Slovakia's bid to join NATO ended
in failure.
</P>
<P>
The Slovak government nullified the referendum because only ten
percent of voters cast ballots.  
</P>
</TEXT>
