visit to China, said that Sino-Italian cooperation will have
bright prospects with joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China and Italy have a good record of economic
cooperation in such areas as petrochemicals, iron and steel,
aviation, and automobiles.
</P>
<P>
A number of cooperative agreements were signed today, he said,
and the two sides have great potential in cooperation in
medium-sized and small enterprises, in addition to that
in major projects.
</P>
<P>
Italy's light industry, textile, and leather technology lead
the world, and China is rich in raw materials and has a huge
market, Li said, noting that cooperation should not be limited to
trade. China and Italy should set up more joint ventures to
cooperate more extensively in leather-tanning and silk printing
and dyeing, he said.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said that he has held constructive and fruitful talks
with Li, and the two sides signed a number of important
cooperative agreements.
</P>
<P>
He said that Italy has always attached great importance to its
relations with China, he said, and the two countries' economies
complement each other, so the two sides can enhance economic
cooperation in various forms.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Italy and China will continue to
enhance their relations in all areas including politics, the
economy, and culture.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo was also present at the
meeting. 
