<HEADLINE> Indonesian Industries Asked to Minimize Waste </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto here
today called on all industries to minimize their wastes while the
country endeavors to produce environment-friendly products which
will improve the competitive edge of its goods on the global
market.
</P>
<P>
After presenting environmental awards to a number of
individuals and regional administrations, the president said that
production of environment-friendly products must be part of the
industries' foundation, policy and strategy which in turn develop
the quality of Indonesian products.
</P>
<P>
He also hailed the increasing number of people involved in
conserving the environment, saying that their efforts have helped
the government a lot in addressing the increasingly formidable and
complicated environmental and development issues.
</P>
<P>
However, Soeharto said that in spite of the efforts, the global
environment is deteriorating.
</P>
<P>
"This is happening because of limited funds despite rapid
progress in science and technology,' he added.
</P>
<P>
"A developing country faces environmental problems due to its
backwardness, unawareness and inability, while a developed country
faces the same problems because of their extravagant use of
natural resources,' he noted.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto said there are 1.7 billion people, mainly in the
developing countries, who do not enjoy clean water because of lack
of funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
