<HEADLINE> Hammer Throw Record Ratified by IAAF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The world record of 69.00 meters in
women's hammer throw was ratified by the International Amateur
Athletics Federation in Monte Carlo, Monaco on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
However, the new mark was destined to be short-lived.
</P>
<P>
Mihaela Melinte of Romania set the new world mark on February
22 in Bucharest and then surpassed the best with a throw of 69.58
meters on March 8, also in Bucharest.
</P>
<P>
The IAAF said Melinte's latest mark was still pending approval
but was expected to be certified in the next several weeks.
</P>
<P>
The old mark was 68.16 meters set by Russian Olga Kuzenkova on
June 18, 1995, in Moscow. 
</P>
