government's Poverty Alleviation Program. Hoechst wants to be a
good corporate citizen in China, he said, and to contribute to the
improvement of the Chinese people's living standard. Hoechst has
set up 22 joint ventures in China so far.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Relations Liu
Shanzai praised the company for its efforts to promote investment
and economic growth in under-developed central and western parts
of China. 
