<HEADLINE> German Industrial Orders Surge 3.3 Percent in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Industrial orders in Germany rose
sharply by 3.3 percent in April over March, the German Economics
Ministry reported today.
</P>
<P>
While foreign orders went up 3.6 percent, domestic demand also
surged 3.1 percent -- a good sign for the economy which has
depended mainly on export-led growth so far this year, analysts
said,
</P>
<P>
Official data published earlier today showed only a 0.6 percent
annual growth in domestic demand in the first quarter, and a 6.8
percent increase in exports.
</P>
<P>
Short-term inflation-adjusted two-month figures showed that
orders in the March-April period soared by 5.4 percent over the
same period last year. 
</P>
