for Water Resources Rajiv Parajuli and his Indian counterpart S.
Venugopalachari, provides Nepal the access of its electricity to
the Indian market.
</P>
<P>
The two governments also signed letters for the exchange of
ratification instruments of a bilateral treaty on the integration
of the Mahakali border river, which lies about 450 km west of
here.
</P>
<P>
Three memorandums of understanding (MOUs) signed here today
between Nepal and India cover civil aviation cooperation and
Indian assisted projects in Nepal, according to the press release.
</P>
<P>
Under the MOU on civil aviation, which revises provisions of
the existing air service agreement between the two countries,
designated airlines of Nepal and India could increase their total
seat capacity to each other's country from the current 4,000 seats
to 6,000 seats per week.  
