<DOCNO> XIE19970605.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EC Proposes Action Plan on Rare Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A five-year European program to
tackle rare diseases and support victims has been launched by the
European Union.
</P>
<P>
The program has three main focus areas, including the provision
of better information about rare diseases, the setting up and
fostering of voluntary organizations to support people affected by
rare diseases.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission said today rare diseases are
life-threatening or chronically debilitating diseases which are of
such low prevalence -- five or less per 10,000 in the population
-- that special efforts are needed if they are to be tackled
effectively.
</P>
<P>
It says that action at European level is of particular value
because the low incidence in every EU member state can be
aggregated to form a much larger group sharing the same
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
This will provide the opportunity to undertake a wider range of
intervention and to initiate co-ordinated action with patients who
might otherwise be isolated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
