<HEADLINE> Striking Workers in Zambian Hospital Return to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Striking workers in Zambia's biggest
hospital return to work today after the hospital management promised
to address their problem within one week.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 general workers of the University Teaching Hospital (UTH),
the biggest hospital in Zambia, went on strike on Tuesday, demanding
payment of salary arrears including their May salaries and five months
of arrears of the 30 percent increment awarded to civil servants by
the government in January this year.
</P>
<P>
The arrears had been paid to all other civil servants in the
country by the end of last month and the UTH workers wondered why they
had been left out. 
