<HEADLINE> Iranian President-Elect Favors Easing Tension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President-elect Mohammad
Khatami said here today that Iran favors easing tension in
relations with other countries and has always strived for
honorable peace.
</P>
<P>
Addressing hundreds of thousands of people who had gathered
at the Mausoleum of the late spiritual leader Khomeini, in
southern Tehran, the 54-year-old president-elect called for a
united front to ward off these threats, saying that all forces
from every wing and faction should work in unity to repel these
threats.
</P>
<P>
"We have always been for an honorable peace coupled with
dignity and independence of the country and to this end the
Islamic Iran has followed and will always pursue a policy of
easing tension in its relations with other countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Iranian nation in the past has incurred
damage and losses from terrorism and thus will strive for a
lasting peace in the world which guarantees the independence and
rights of all nations.
</P>
<P>
Khatami, who won the presidency by securing 69 percent of a
total of 29.07 million votes cast on May 23, called on all
revolutionary forces and those sympathetic with the Islamic
revolution to cooperate with government officials for the success
of the next administration which is due to take over in August.
</P>
<P>
He said that the continuation of the reconstruction programs,
promotion of social justice and safeguarding the dignity of Iran
will be top on the agenda of his government.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that he will carry out his platform to further
enhance the prestige of the country with full commitment to
Islam, the supreme leader and the nation under the guidance of
the leader of the Islamic revolution.
</P>
<P>
"Success in this task is not possible without an overall
partnership of the people and precise supervision of Parliament
and public institutions as well as the press over the
performance of the government and its officials," he added.
</P>
<P>
"Healthy and constructive criticism of government's
performance by the press will enable the administration to
strengthen its strong points and drop the weak points," Khatami
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"What is of utmost importance is respect for the rule of law
and the rights stipulated in the constitution of the Islamic
Republic of Iran," Khatami was quoted by the official news
agency IRNA as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the society needs a strong government whose strength
is derived from adherence to law.
</P>
<P>
He said that going ahead with reconstruction efforts,
promoting the dignity and independence of the country demand
national determination which will come by respecting the
law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
