<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets US Visitor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
today that China and the United States share the responsibility of
working hard to bring a healthy and stable Sino-US relationship
into the next century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark here this afternoon with Zbigniew
Brzezinski, former special assistant to the President for National
Security Affairs of the US.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that Brzezinski took part in the work for the
establishment of Sino-US diplomatic ties during his term of
office and made
contributions to the normalization of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
After that, he still worked extensively to promote the
development of bilateral relations, Jiang said, adding he
appreciated Brzezinski's efforts.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the world is moving towards multi-polarization,
which plays an important role in promoting world peace, stability
and development. Meanwhile, he said, the international community
still faces many unstable elements and numerous challenges.
</P>
<P>
Under such a global situation, China and the US, as two big
countries in the world and two permanent members of the Security
Council of the United Nations, share more comprehensive common
interests and more responsibilities, compared with a dozen years
ago when the two sides forged diplomatic ties, Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that at the dawn of a new century, the nature
of the Sino-US relationship that continues into the next century
is a great historical mission for the leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"We share the responsibility of working hard to bring a
healthy and stable Sino-US relationship into the 21st century,"
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Sino-US relations have shown a trend toward improvement since
the latter half of last year, Jiang noted, adding that whether the
opportunity can be seized to promote a healthy and steady
development of bilateral relations requires not only the concerted
efforts from the two governments but also the active efforts from
people of insight of various circles of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his hope that Brzezinski may continue to play a
active role in promoting the further improvement and development
of Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Brzezinski said that three years have passed since his last
visit to China, and China's great changes have proved it is a
country of vitality, which has made a deep impression on him.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his feeling that in the years to come, China will
continue to concentrate on developing the economy and improving
Chinese people's life.
</P>
<P>
He said the notion spreading throughout the world that China
will adopt an overbearing position in international affairs is
groundless and does not accord with the reality.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the US-China relationship is one of the most
important bilateral relationships in the current world, Brzezinski
said that a full range of common interests exist between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that leaders of the two countries should increase their
dialogue on issues of strategic importance, and work hard so that
the two peoples can understand and support these common interests,
and the bilateral relations may be built on a more solid and
comprehensive base.
</P>
<P>
Among those present on the occasion were Liu Huaqiu, director
of the Foreign Affairs Office of the State Council, Mei Zhaorong,
president of the Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs,
and James Ralph Sasser, US ambassador to China.
</P>
<P>
Brzezinski is here as the guest of the Chinese People's
Institute of Foreign Affairs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
