<HEADLINE> HK Grounded Airbuses Re-enter Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's flagcarrier Cathay
Pacific put four of its grounded A330-300s back to service today
after the fleet's temporary suspension.
</P>
<P>
These aircraft have been fitted with modifications to gearboxes
in their Rolls-Royce Trent 700 engines, thus eliminating the
bearing lubrication problem which led to the suspension of A330
operations 13 days ago.
</P>
<P>
Cathay announced today that 10 of its fleet of 11 A330s were
positioned outside Hong Kong when operations were suspended on May
24. All are currently being fitted with the modified gearboxes and
will each be ferried back to Hong Kong to operate their first
commercial flights from the airline's home base.
</P>
<P>
The entire A330 fleet of Cathay Pacific is expected to be back
in service by the end of this week, earlier than the airline had
predicted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
