<HEADLINE> China to Recruit More Overseas Talents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China plans to recruit about
170,000 overseas experts and send around 90,000 people to attend
overseas training programs in the coming two years, according to
China's State Bureau of Foreign Experts (SBFE).
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, some 160,000 cultural, technical and
managerial experts have worked in China. Among them about 120,000
worked in foreign-financed enterprises, SBFE director Wan Xueyuan
told a national talent introduction conference, which ended here
today.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, State Councillor Li Guixian urged
departments concerned to bring the talent search to a higher level
so as to better serve the country's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Wan said that China's move to recruit overseas talent in the
next two years will focus on serving agriculture and the reform
of the large and medium-sized state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Overseas talent will also be brought to the country to serve
China's science and education drive and accelerate the training of
highly-qualified professionals, Wan said.  
</P>
