<HEADLINE> World Cup Skiing Champion Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Alpine Frenchman skier Luc Alphand,
the overall World Cup champion, said on Thursday he was retiring
from the sport.
</P>
<P>
Alphand, 31, said he would retire after the Winter Olympics in
February next year in Nagano, Japan, saying "it was not an easy
decision to take."
</P>
<P>
The Frenchman said "eighty percent of the people around me
wanted me to carry on but I have a family to look after."
</P>
<P>
Alphand, in a career of 13 years, became the first Frenchman in
March to win the overall World Cup since 1968. 
