<HEADLINE> Nigerian Army Doctor Invents Blood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A Nigerian army doctor,
Lieutenant-Colonel Oviemo Ovadje, has recently invented an
emergency blood auto-transfusion set.
</P>
<P>
The device named EATSET can be used for rapid removal of blood
from victims of internal hemorrhage as well as the re-infusion
of the patient's blood, according to local press reports.
</P>
<P>
It also prevents transmission of diseases, checks
immunological complications of homologous transfusion and permits
greater flexibility in the use of blood supplies.
</P>
<P>
Two hundred units of EATSET have been used by doctors in the
World Health Organization headquarters in Geneva for clinical
tests and trials, reports said. 
</P>
