<HEADLINE> China Hopes for Smooth Transfer of Defense Affairs in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China hopes that Britain will adopt
a sincere attitude toward cooperation with the Chinese side to
ensure the smooth transfer of defense affairs in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Cui Tiankai told today's
routine news briefing that the Chinese government will resume its
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong starting from July 1, 1997,
in accordance with the Sino-British Joint Declaration, and that Hong
Kong should be handed over from the British government to the
Chinese government from the same date.
</P>
<P>
Cui noted that the joint declaration also stipulates the
central government of China will be in charge of Hong Kong's
defense affairs from July 1.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese People's Liberation Army will carry out their
mission on defense affairs in Hong Kong region from zero hour of
July 1, in order to effectively implement the Sino-British Joint
Declaration as well as to fulfill the smooth transfer of defense
affairs in Hong Kong," he stated.
</P>
<P>
"The two sides are still consulting on certain specific issues,
and China hopes that the British side will engage in sincere
cooperation with the Chinese side to make proper arrangements, so
as to ensure the smooth transfer of defense affairs in Hong Kong,
Cui said, noting that "the smooth transfer of defense affairs in
Hong Kong also constitutes a very important part of Hong Kong's
smooth transfer of power."  
</P>
</TEXT>
