<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao to Establish Information Network Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A joint information network center
will be established in Macao before the end of this year to
facilitate the exchange of information between China's interior
areas and Macao, and other parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
An agreement was signed here Wednesday by three parties
involved -- the Macao Foundation, China's State Science and
Technology Commission (SSTC) and the Macao-based International
Institute of Software Technology of the United Nations University.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the SSTC will provide computers,
the UN institute will supply technical services, and the Macao
Foundation will be in charge of management of the Macao
Information-Net Center.
</P>
<P>
Wu Guoxiang, an expert who signed the agreement on behalf of
the SSTC, said that the center will enable users of the Internet
to have a quicker access to information on China's interior
areas and Macao.
</P>
<P>
"It is now difficult to get access to information about China
via the Internet in China because communications facilities are
not so good," Wu told Xinhua. "Macao's communications facilities,
 however, are much better."
</P>
<P>
World Internet users can, via the center, get a quicker contact
with relevant departments in China's interior areas while the
latter can spread information on science and technology, economic
affairs and business information via the center, he said.
</P>
<P>
The center will also benefit Macao, he added. It will help
spread information about Macao, expand its information service so
that Macao will gradually become a hub of international business
service.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the center is set to start operation before
1998 as further negotiations are still under way.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
