<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exports Revenue Increases in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' exports revenue
reached 2.082 billion U.S. dollars in April 1997, a 39.6 percent
increase over the same period of last year, the National
Statistics Office said today.
</P>
<P>
In a report released here, the office said that when compared
to the previous month, April's exports revenue rose by 4.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
Exports of electronics and components, accounting for 43.9
percent of the total, rose by 48 percent in the month to 913.44
million dollars from 617.34 million dollars in April last year, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The second biggest earner, with an eight percent share, was
articles of apparel and clothing accessories, which had an
aggregate income of 166.57 million dollars, or 6.1 percent higher
than that of April 1996, it said.
</P>
<P>
Value of exports from January to April this year grew by 22.8
percent to 7.588 billion dollars compared with the corresponding
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The United States, Japan, Singapore and the Netherlands are the
country's major importers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
