<HEADLINE> S. Korean President's Son Indicted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 5 (Xinhua) -- South Korean prosecutors today
indicted Kim Hyun-chul, the second son of President Kim Young-sam,
on bribery and tax evasion.
</P>
<P>
The junior Kim's close aide Kim Ki-sup, former deputy director
of the National Security Planning, was also indicted on graft
charges.
</P>
<P>
The trial for the president's son and his five aides is
expected to open early next month, according to court officials.
</P>
<P>
The 38-year-old junior Kim was arrested on May 17 on charges of
taking 3.6 million U.S. dollars in return for favors from two
business firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
