<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Minimum Wage Increased in Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Zanzibar government on
Wednesday raised the minimum wage pushing it to 20,000 Tanzania
Shillings (about 33.3 US Dollars) from present 15,000 T.Shs.
(about 25 US Dollars) per month, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Minister for Finance, Amina Salum Ali announced the new
wage structure in the House of Representatives when presenting
1997/98 government budget proposals in the town of Zanzibar.
</P>
<P>
She said procedures to adjust the salaries in the civil
service would be made public after consultation with accounting
officers and governemtn institutions.
</P>
<P>
In the case of private sector, Ali said the government has
enacted a law on the minimum wage for employees in the sector.
</P>
<P>
The minister also announced the establishment of Social
Security Fund (SSF) to offer economic and social protection to
employees upon retirement.
</P>
<P>
A bill to that effect is being prepared, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
