<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai FM Expresses Confidence in Hong Kong's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab
Chaiyasarn here today expressed confidence in the future of Hong
Kong, while foreseeing greater opportunities for Thailand to
promote its economic exchanges with it.
</P>
<P>
The Thai foreign minister reiterated the Thai government's
views on Hong Kong in an exclusive interview with Xinhua reporters
in Bangkok at the Thai Foreign Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
"Thailand and Hong Kong have agreed to extend mutual visa
exemption up to 30 days to passport holders of Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HK SAR) and Thailand respectively," he
said, adding this represents Thailand's solid vote of confidence
for the future of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Prachuab also highlighted the significance of Hong Kong's
return to China, noting that a successful transition for Hong Kong
will enhance China's international reputation.
</P>
<P>
On the "one country, two systems" policy, Prachuab said that
the policy initiated by the late Deng Xiaoping is the right
formula for the integration of Hong Kong into China in view of
Hong Kong's history and reality.
</P>
<P>
The policy will help China uphold national unity and
territorial integrity while maintaining the prosperity and
stability of Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the future Thai-Hong Kong relations, Prachuab said
that Thailand and Hong Kong have enjoyed close ties in trade,
business, investment and tourism for decades, as it enjoys
excellent relationship with the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong to China will increase the economic
potential of our relations further by providing additional options
in our economic interaction," he said.
</P>
<P>
"After the handover, Thailand will continue to cooperate
closely with 'Hong Kong, China' in various international
organizations and trade agreements because it is our mutual
benefit to do so," he added.
</P>
<P>
Prachuab also expressed confidence in the HK SAR Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa's ability to handle the region's affairs.
</P>
<P>
Prachuab said he had met with Tung before and described him as
a successful businessman. He believed that Tung could also be a
good politician.  
</P>
</TEXT>
