<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Urges to further Use Deng's Theory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Deng Xiaoping has left abundant and
valuable ideological wealth to the Chinese people and his theory
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics should continue
to be practiced, a senior Chinese leader urged recently.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
made the remarks during an inspection tour in Shanxi Province in
the north.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, the senior CPC leader, who is also chairman of
the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC), visited a number of major projects and heard reports by
senior provincial officials on the local development.
</P>
<P>
In his talks with local officials, Qiao praised both cadres and
the masses of people in the province for the spirit of forging
ahead as well as for their hard and strenuous efforts in their
economic development, saying that the provincial leadership has
worked out its development strategy in line with the specific
local conditions.
</P>
<P>
Still greater changes are due to take place in Shanxi, if the
local people carry out Deng's theory and the Party's basic line,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of studying Deng Xiaoping's theory, he said, is to
apply it into the social practice of hundreds of millions of the
Chinese people, so as to effectively advance China's socialist
modernization program.
</P>
<P>
While affirming Shanxi's active exploration of the reform in
the state-owned enterprises, Qiao called for pushing forward the
state-owned enterprise reform by making effective efforts and
adopting practical measures and resolving problems thoroughly.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the pace for legislation should be accelerated in
Shanxi, supervisory work be effectively strengthened, and some
good experience created, summed up and further improved, Qiao Shi
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
