<DOCNO> XIE19970605.0155 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Go Down on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to go
lower on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials fell another 4.18 points to close at 2043.71 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume was thin at 125.23 million units, worth
397.74 million Singapore dollars (about 278.14 million U.S.
dollars). Declines led advances by a narrow margin of 154 to 153,
while 315 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Local fruit and food trading firm FHTK was the most actively
traded stock as it registered a turnover of 8.91 million units. It
was followed by the Hong Kong Land which had 7.09 million shares
traded. The Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign was next
with 5.57 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
City Developments led the gainers of the day as it rose 40
cents to finish at 11.1 Singapore dollars. JMH 400, the United
Overseas Bank (UOB) F A and UOB Foreign gained 30 cents each to
end at 7.35, 15.6, and 15.8 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation
(OCBC) Foreign was the biggest loser as it plunged 3.2 Singapore
dollars to close at 15.2 dollars. OCBC fell 1.75 dollars to finish
at 8.05 Singapore dollars, while Creative 50 ended 1.5 Singapore
dollars lower at 23.6 dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
