<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Social Security System Perfected In Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in north China
has made headway in the reform of its social security system,
forming a management network for the job, Deputy Provincial
Governor Ye Liansong said recently.
</P>
<P>
The system now covers not only pension and unemployment
insurance, but also that for on-the-job injuries, medicare, and
birth. Insurance expenses are borne jointly by the country,
enterprises, and individuals, instead of by state and enterprises
as before.
</P>
<P>
A provincial social security committee and a supervisory
committee on a social security insurance fund were established in
1996 to further improve the system.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, more than 90 percent of the province's
workers had taken part in the social mutual assistance fund, and
approximately 30,000 enterprises had purchased unemployment
insurance.
</P>
<P>
More than 80 counties and cities across the province have set
up self-management organizations for retired employees.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970605.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Greater Efforts for Treasury Bond Issue  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shang attributed the slowdown in bond sales to a capital
diversion to a surging stock market since the start of this year.
</P>
<P>
A huge capital inflow into the stock market is a major factor
affecting the smooth floatation of treasury bonds, he said.
</P>
<P>
The stock indices had soared more than 45 percent each at
China's two stock exchanges in Shanghai and Shenzhen before the
release of a government regulation banning state enterprises and
listed companies from speculating in stocks on May 21.
</P>
<P>
Shang added that another important reason for the slowdown in
bonds sales is an expanded planned issue of corporate bonds.
</P>
<P>
China has officially set this year's quota of corporate bonds
at 15 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
An widely overlapping availability period of corporate bonds
and treasury bonds in the first half of this year combined with a
higher interest rate for the corporate bonds have made treasury
bonds less attractive to investors, Shang said.
</P>
<P>
Both officials said that more should be done to complete the
floatation of treasury bonds already announced, as another 60
billion yuan in government bonds will have to be issued in the
second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The issuing speed must be accelerated in order to sell out all
bonds when the year ends, they urged.
</P>
<P>
"The floatation of treasury bonds is a important issue that has
a bearing on the overall situation of the economic work," Liu
said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shang said that the successful completion of the
treasury bond issues will be in the interest of meeting the
objectives of the financial and monetary policies.
</P>
<P>
It also will help reduce investment risks, the deputy central
bank governor noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
