<HEADLINE> India to Elect New President Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Indian Election Commission
announced here today that the election of the 10th president for
the country will be held on July 14.
</P>
<P>
The tenure of President Shanker Dayal Sharma comes to an end on
July 24 this year.
</P>
<P>
The Election College for Presidential Election comprises 4,848
members -- 543 members of the Lok Sabha (the lower house of the
parliament), 233 of the Rajya Sabha (the upper house of the
parliament) and 4,072 members of the state assemblies.
</P>
<P>
Under the Presidential and Vice-Presidential Elections Act
(1952), the election to the office of president is held according
to the system of proportional representation by means of a single
transferable vote. Voting would be conducted by secret ballot.
</P>
</TEXT>
