<HEADLINE> China Sets up Marine Resource Utilization Demonstration Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- the Chinese Ministry of Finance
and National Bureau of Oceanography have decided to set four
eastern coastal cities as the country's demonstration zones for
utilization and administration of marine resources.
</P>
<P>
The four cities are Zhoushan City of Zhejiang Province, Yantai
City of Shandong Province, Huludao City in Liaoning Province, and
Qinhuangdao City of Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The four areas are required to formulate strict regulations on
utilization and administration of marine resources.
</P>
<P>
The zones are being established to lay a basis for the
country's legislation on utilization and administration of marine
resources.
</P>
<P>
The four zones are investigating the situation of their marine
industry, oil and chemical engineering projects, coastal tourism,
land reclamation, construction safety areas, exploration of marine
minerals, discharge of polluted materials from land and
installation of seabed cables. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
