<DOCNO> XIE19970605.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines to Burn Textbooks Filled With Errors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Department of
Education, Culture and Sports said here today that it would burn
all textbooks filled with errors in Cebu, the second biggest city
of the country.
</P>
<P>
Education Undersecretary Antonio Nachura said that all
error-filled textbooks found in Cebu would be withdrawn and burnt
next week.
</P>
<P>
As a symbolic gesture of the drive against the use of these
books, the education department will send Undersecretary Erlinda
Pefianco to oversee the burning, Nachura added.
</P>
<P>
The assurance came in the light of a report by Representative
Raul del Mar of the proliferation of such books in Cebu.
</P>
<P>
Del Mar said in a statement that in Cebu, all of the 36 books
used in private and public schools, except those used in Grades 5
and 6, "contain material errors in facts, grammar and concepts."
</P>
<P>
Some of the more glaring examples of errors were the reference
of national hero Apolinario Mabini as a "she", utilization of some
words which are non-existent in the dictionary and the employment
of torture on grasshoppers and ducks, he said.
</P>
<P>
Nachura said he is waiting for a policy statement from
Education Secretary Ricardo Gloria on whether legal action will be
taken against those found responsible for the error-filled
textbooks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
