<HEADLINE> New Communications Systems Built in Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A short-wave weather communications
system, a key state high-tech project, has passed appraisal and is
being built in Xi'an, capital of northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The advanced system will be in wide use.
</P>
<P>
Its communications radius is over 1,000 kilometers, which
solves the problems encountered by other traditional
communications systems.
</P>
<P>
Developed by Xi'an Dazhong Communications Engineering
Corporation and Xi'an University of Science and Technology with
two million yuan (nearly 250,000 US dollars) of funds, the system
can also be used in military, public security, oil and ocean
transportation fields.
</P>
<P>
So far, only a few developed countries including the US can
produce the same sort of system.  
</P>
