<HEADLINE> China's 1st Archipelago Airport Ready for Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The construction of Zhoushan
Zhujiajian Airport, the first airport built on one of China's
archipelagos, has been completed and it is expected to become
operational by July this year, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Zhoushan Archipelago, with over 1,300 islands, is the largest
archipelago in the country and Zhoushan City was made a coastal
open city by the central government in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Airport construction started in 1993, which covers over 200
hectares. and costs 344 million yuan. Its 2,500-long runways can
land passenger aircraft like Boeing-737s and MD-82s.
</P>
<P>
Initially, eight flights, linking Zhoushan with Xiamen,
Shanghai, Beijing, Guangzhou and Shenzhen cities, will be opened.
</P>
