<HEADLINE> Work on Coastline Super-highway Quickened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Work has sped up in the
construction of the Ningbo section, of a 5,300 km coastline
super-highway that runs across the country.
</P>
<P>
The expressway which starts from Sanya of Hainan province in
the southern tip and ends at Tongjiang, Heilongjiang province in
northeast China, is scheduled to go into operation by the end of
this century. It will become a key transport artery along the
country's coastal areas.
</P>
<P>
The Ningbo section of the road, with four lanes, is 145.5
kilometers long. Its designed speed will reach 100 to 120
kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
Construction on the section started in October of 1995. The
project involves an estimated investment of 5.2 billion yuan in
total.
</P>
<P>
The roadbed project from Daqian to Dazhujia, in northern part
of Ningbo section, is finished. The road, with a length of 28.8
kilometers, is expected to open for service by the end of next
year.
</P>
<P>
The Panhuo overpass adjacent to Dazhujia, which connects the
road to the Hangzhou-Ningbo expressway, will be built this
September.
</P>
<P>
Work on all other parts of Ningbo section has already begun or
will soon begin, sources say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
