<HEADLINE> Test-Tube Calves In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Two test-tube calves, a male and a
female, were born recently on the grassland of Shilingol, North
China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Xu Rigan, academician of Chinese Academy of Engineering
(CAE), and president of Inner Mongolia University, was in charge
of this new bio-technology project. He succeeded in reproducing
the world's first test-tube goat in Japan years ago.
</P>
<P>
The successful experiment marks the beginning of the real-world
apllication of the technology in China.
</P>
<P>
The advanced bio-technology is expected to change the country's
long cycle and low efficiency in cultivating fine-breed livestock,
and promote the country's livestock farming. 
