<HEADLINE> General Electric Sets up Finance Company in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China's central bank has approved
an application by the General Electric Finance Corp. of the United
States to set up a finance company in Shanghai, according to
official sources.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the new company, known as GE Finance and
Accounting (China) Co. Ltd, raised to 48 the number of operational
overseas financial institutions in Shanghai, China's leading
economic and financial center.
</P>
<P>
The business scope of the GE company, to be located in the
city's Pudong New Area, includes accepting deposits and extending
loans in foreign exchange, discounting bills in foreign exchange,
providing foreign exchange-based guarantees, making investments,
offering trust, trading in foreign exchange, raising and leasing
funds in foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
Official records show that the 48 overseas financial
institutions are from 15 countries and regions; more than 20 are
banks ranking among the world's biggest 50 in terms of assets.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of representative offices set up in
Shanghai by overseas financial institutions has reached more than
160.
</P>
<P>
Official figures also show that the Shanghai-based operational
overseas banks and financial companies had a total of 13.5 billion
US dollars in assets by the end of last year, up 49 percent over a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
Loans in foreign exchange extended by the overseas financial
institutions soared 50 percent on a yearly basis to nine billion
US dollars in 1996. Their deposits and profits grew six and 41
percent last year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that overseas insurance companies in
Shanghai reported more than 500 million yuan in premium income in
1996.
</P>
<P>
Observers say that as China's opening-up in the financial
sector deepens, Shanghai is drawing greater attention worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is currently the only Chinese city where some overseas
banks are allowed to deal in business in the Chinese currency.
</P>
</TEXT>
