<HEADLINE> China Starts Building Marine Science Experiment Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China has begun construction of the
marine science experiment base of the State National Bureau of
Oceanoagraphy in the eastern coastal city of Qingdao.
</P>
<P>
The experiment base has six parts including a scientific
research area, Sino-foreign academic exchanges and cooperation
area, and a new-technology business area.
</P>
<P>
The base occupies 8.8 hectares on land. Its first phase
construction, to be completed in 1999, includes a lab building, a
library, and some capital construction projects.
</P>
<P>
China Ocean News quoted an official with the National Bureau of
Oceangraphy as saying that the building of the base will promote
Sino-foreign cooperation on ocean development, speeding up marine
investigations and building of major labs for marine scientific
research.  
</P>
