<HEADLINE> Exhibition Shows World Bank-funded Research Findings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 5 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition on the achievements
of research projects funded by the World Bank opened today in
Fudan University in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 people, including government officials and
representatives from some 50 research institutes across the
country attended the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, the World Bank has put 130 million US dollars in
financing China's 75 key state laboratories, 58 specialized labs
and the computer center of the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The achievements are related to energy, raw materials, new
materials, transportation, manufacturing and control systems of
machinery, electronics, telecommunication, agriculture, biological
technology, medicine, environmental protection, and disaster
management.
</P>
<P>
A two-day forum to be participated by Chinese and overseas
specialists will be held during the 10-day exhibition.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is sponsored by United Nations Development
Program and China International Center for Economic and
Technological Exchanges. 
</P>
