<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Ethnic Minority Prospering In Han-dominated Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Ethnic minorities in central
China's Henan province have made big contributions to local
economic development.
</P>
<P>
The 50 ethnic minority groups scattered all over the province
contributed four percent to Henan's GNP last year, while their
population of 1.13 million accounts for only 1.24 percent of the
province's total.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic minority people have become a driving force in
developing the province's fur processing, foodstuff production,
and catering services, according to the provincial nationalities
affairs commission.
</P>
<P>
Among 20 ethnic minority autonomous townships, 16 produce more
than 100 million yuan in output value, and farmers in 15 of them
enjoy over 1,000 yuan in per-capita income.
</P>
<P>
The Changhe Hui Township of Luoyang city produced billion yuan
worth of output value to become a local economic giant.
</P>
<P>
The province has 401 ethnic minority villages, and 25 percent
of them have become comfortably well-off, much higher than the
provincial average.
</P>
<P>
Some ethnic minorities have expanded their small workshops to
large-scale high-tech enterprises, some of which have been
transformed into export-oriented stock companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
