<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Russian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), said that the CPC is ready to
promote its friendly relations with the Communist Party of the
Russian Federation (CPRF).
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, said this at a meeting here today with a delegation
from the CPRF headed by Valentin A. Kuptsov, first Vice-Chairman
of the CPRF.
</P>
<P>
Hu said it is of great significance for China and Russia, two
influential countries in the world and good neighbors to each
other, to establish and develop a strategic and cooperative
partnership oriented towards the 21st century. This partnership
will not only serve the fundamental interest of the two countries,
but also global peace and stability as well as the establishment
of a just political and economic order in the world, he added
</P>
<P>
Hu went on to say that to enhance Sino-Russian exchanges
through different channels and in various areas, including contact
between political parties, will help promote a new-type of
state-to-state relationship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Hu also briefed the visitors on the CPC's current operations.
</P>
<P>
Kuptsov told Hu that the delegation hopes to be better
acquainted with the achievements and experience scored by the CPC
in building the Party and the country. The CPRF will continue to
strengthen its friendly relations with the CPC and promote
cooperation between the two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Kuptsov and his party are here on a visit as guest of the CPC.
