<HEADLINE> Promising East China Wheat Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Shandong Province is expected to
harvest 20.5 billion kg of wheat this year, the province's
agricultural department disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say they are confident of reaping this year an
improved per-hectare wheat yield, estimated at an average of 5,100
kg, though the province grew less wheat, only 4.03 million
hectares, a drop of 6,666 hectares from last year's.
</P>
<P>
The province has planned to invest 3.5 billion yuan in grain
production and farming this year, a rise of 500 million yuan over
last year's level, and to increase grain purchases from farmers,
and raise output by a wide application of advanced growing
techniques, to ensure a full success of the province's agriculture
in 1997, said the officials.
</P>
<P>
Shandong, one of China's leading grain producers and chief
wheat production base, produced 43.3 billion kg of grain last
year. 
</P>
