<HEADLINE> Hebei Province Expects Strong Wheat Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province, one of North
China's major grain producers, expects an imminent bumper wheat
harvest after expanding its wheat growing area to its largest
since 1980.
</P>
<P>
Li Lianxi, a provincial agricultural official, said that
Hebei's wheat growing area was increased by nearly 100,000 ha to
2.687 million ha, and that farmers chose to grow more wheat this
year because last year's severe flood had created good moist
condition in the soil.
</P>
<P>
Hebei, which usually suffers droughts every year, is enjoying
abundant rainfall this spring, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The official also attributes strengthened combat against
insects and wheat disease to a certain bumper harvest. He added
that farmers will soon start cutting in the wheat. 
</P>
