<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 12 Teams to Take Part in Copa American Soccer Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Twelve Latin American soccer
teams will compete in the Copa America championship which will be
held in five Bolivian cities from June 11 to 29.
</P>
<P>
Group A is made up of teams from Chile, Argentina, Ecuador and
Paraguay and will be based in the city of Cochabamba.
</P>
<P>
Group B, made up of teams from Bolivia, Peru, Uruguay and
Venezuela, will be based in the city of Sucre.
</P>
<P>
The tropical city of Santa Cruz, located in the middle of the
continent, will play host to Group C that will include Colombia,
Brazil, Mexico and Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
Additional games will be played in Oruro and La Paz. The finals
will be played either in Santa Cruz or La Paz. 
</P>
