<HEADLINE> Thai High-end Textile Products Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports of high-end
textile and garment products jumped 22.8 percent to 307 million US
dollars) in the first quarter this year when compared with the
same period last year, according to Thai Commerce Minister
Narongchai Akrasanee.
</P>
<P>
Narongchai was quoted today by local press as saying that the
high-end textile were exported under quota agreements with Canada,
the European union, Norway and the United States.
</P>
<P>
He said the better export performance were mainly due to
economic upturns in the importing countries. It was also due to
the fact that exporters had successfully upgraded their products
from low-end to high-end status.
</P>
<P>
However, the country's exports of low-end goods slowed 20
percent in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
Narongchai said his ministry was promoting those products in
neighboring Indochina to try to boost exports.
</P>
<P>
In the past, the major markets for Thailand's low-end garments
were Eastern Europe and the Middle East but these regions have
increasingly been buying cheaper goods from China, Indonesia and
Vietnam.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
