<DOCNO> XIE19970605.0253 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Automobile Products Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The value of Thailand's exports of
automobile products jumped 121.47 percent to 6,483.37 million baht
(259 million US dollars) in the first four months this year
compared with the same period last year, according to the
Federation of Thai Industries' Automobile Industry Club.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's automobile products exports were valued at 3,555.95
million baht (142 million US dollars) in the first four months
last year.
</P>
<P>
Products included assembled cars, motorcycles, engines, and
interior and spare parts.
</P>
<P>
Car exports for the period totaled 9,137 worth 2,915.02 million
baht (116.6 million US dollars), a jump of 636.85 percent in
quantity and 860.34 percent in value from the same period of last
year respectively.
</P>
<P>
Car engine exports and other auto contents reaped 528.13
million baht (21 million US dollars) and 692.55 baht (27.7 million
US dollars) for the period, a surge of 135.19 percent and 234.39
percent from the corresponding period last year respectively.
</P>
<P>
Motorcycle exports totaled 44,036 worth 1,478.74 million baht
(59 million US dollars) for the period, down by 35.18 percent and
28.59 percent form last year.
</P>
<P>
But motorcycle contents and spare parts exports jumped a
massive 680.04 percent and 344.85 percent to 763.5 million baht
(30.5 million US dollars) and 105.43 million baht (4.2 million US
dollars) respectively.
</P>
<P>
Vehicles assembled for the period excluding motorcycles totaled
174,124, down 4.05 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 55,360, or 31.79 percent, were passenger cars, up
by 30.97 from last years share. Some 101,325 one-ton pick-up
trucks were assembled for the period, representing 67.58 percent
of the total automobiles assembled, down by 11.889 percent from
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Motorcycles assembled were also down by 13.95 percent compared
to last year. Of the 441,349 motorcycles assembled, 399,355 were
family-type and 41.994 were sports-type.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
