<HEADLINE> Australia Beats Britain in Champions Trophy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Australia took another step towards
winning their fourth successive Women's Champions Trophy with a
3-0 victory over Britain here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
After soaking up a lot of early pressure and surviving two
early penalty corners the Australians took the lead in the 20th
minute.
</P>
<P>
Britain were caught on the counter-attack as Katrine Powell
claimed the ball in midfield and powered her way down the right
wing and with assistance from Nicole Mott provided the first goal
for Karen Smith.
</P>
<P>
Jennifer Morris scored eight minutes later with a crashing shot
from Australia's third penalty corner, taking full advantage of a
Great Britain side that failed to take its own limited
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Britain piled on the pressure in the first 15 minutes of the
second-half but Australia ensured a fine win with their third as
Powell, having her best match of the tournament, created the
opening for Michelle Andrews.
</P>
<P>
American goalkeeper Andrea Wieland, who had saved her team in
the two previous matches with outstanding performances, had a
nightmare of a game as the United States went down 3-0 to the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Germany secured a controversial 3-2 win over South Korea in
another match on the day when their first goal went in off Nadine
Ernsting-Frienke's foot outside the circle. 
</P>
