<HEADLINE> South China Hi-Tech Park Attracts Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, Jane 5 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Hi-Tech Park in south
China's Guangdong province is becoming one of the key zones for
overseas funds in the area.
</P>
<P>
The place now has more than 200 hi-tech enterprises, most of
which are involved in communications, computers, medicines, and
new materials.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, of 34.76 billion yuan (4.3 billion US dollars) in
total output in Shenzhen's hi-tech sector, nearly 20 percent came
from the park.
</P>
<P>
Li Zibin, the city's mayor, recently told a press conference
that Shenzhen will develop its hi-tech sector even more, and that,
"the development of the hi-tech sector should be viewed as a new
economic growth mechanism for Shenzhen's overall economy."
</P>
<P>
The park is located in the west of the Shenzhen Special
Economic Zone and has a number of research institutes, including
Shenzhen University, the Shenzhen-Qinghua Institute, and the
national electrical engineering center.
</P>
<P>
According to a local source, electronic information,
bio-engineering, new materials, and optically-controlled machine
tools are the park's four major industries, and that electronics
has a certain advantage there.
</P>
<P>
At the end of this year the proportion the hi-tech sector holds
in Shenzhen's total industrial output is expected to be 32
percent, up 3.3 percentage points from last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
