<HEADLINE> Island Garden Wins World Recognition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A tropical garden in south China's
Hainan Province has been cited by world environmental
organizations for its success in the protection of bio-diversity.
</P>
<P>
The Xinglong Tropical Garden, located in southwest Hainan
Island, covers an area of 440 ha. Since 1992, more than 70 million
yuan has been invested in the construction of the garden, now a
tourist resort.
</P>
<P>
The garden is now home to more than 3,000 plant species,
including more than 1,000 rare species imported from overseas.
</P>
<P>
Design, gardening and environmental protection experts have
participated in the construction of the garden.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 53 ha of tropical fruits are planted in the
garden, and a plant museum will soon be built there. 
</P>
