<HEADLINE> US Hi-Tech Company Making Profits In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Seagate Technology International,
a US hard drive manufacturer, expects to double its production and
sales in China this year compared with the previous year.
</P>
<P>
By now, the company has set up two production bases in
China. One of them is located in Shenzhen in South China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
With an investment of 38 million US dollars, the base has
produced more than 10 million disk drives, half of whose
components are manufactured in China. Last year its sale volume
reached 580 million US dollars, and the figure is expected to
double this year.
</P>
<P>
Costing 52 million US dollars, the other base, set up in Wuxi
in east China's Jiangsu Province, has 3,300 employees and had
produced three million disk drives by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
With an investment of 90 million US dollars in China, the US
company occupies more than half of China's hard disk drive
market. 
</P>
