<HEADLINE> Tianjin Residents Benefit From Housing Fund-Raising Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- This major industrial city in north
China has so far pooled 2.42 billion yuan in funds raised by the
public for housing construction, which has markedly improved the
residents' living conditions.
</P>
<P>
According to a local source, some 2.3 million employees from
17,000 city's enterprises and units participated in the housing
fund-raising event.
</P>
<P>
Built with the collected money are new apartments with floor
space totaling over 16 million sq m, which have benefited 300,000
families in the city.
</P>
<P>
To date, the city's average per capita living space has risen
from 3.85 sq m in the 1980s to the present 7.74 sq m, nearing the
national average.
</P>
<P>
The pooling technique has benefitted local residents in other
ways: the fund administration center has so far provided 129
million yuan in low-interest loans to more than 5,000 workers to
buy houses. 
</P>
