<HEADLINE> Light Industry Exports Up in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China's light industry exports for
the January-April period rose 26.1 percent on an annual basis to
14.58 billion US dollars, according to the China National Council
of Light Industry.
</P>
<P>
It reported that bicycle exports grew the most, at almost 200
percent, but that output was down 13.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Ceramic exports rose 56.46 percent, while plastic products,
toys, lighting equipment. and embroidered silk were above the
national average.
</P>
<P>
Of the 25 major light industrial products, 14 registered growth
in output during the January-April period, with vacuum cleaners,
refrigerators, and washing machines at the head of the growth,
while electric fans, aluminum ware, and canned food saw the
biggest decrease in output.
</P>
<P>
Light industry achieved 58 billion yuan in added value during
the period, 8.5 percent up on a yearly basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
