<HEADLINE> Gansu Promote All-round Social Insurance System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A comprehensive social insurance
system covering the aged, unemployed, job injuries, medical
care and child-bearing has initially taken shape in northwest
China's Gansu province.
</P>
<P>
So far, some 920,000 employees from over 10,000 enterprises and
units in the province, or 95 percent of the total, have
participated in the unified old-age insurance program.
</P>
<P>
And 1.27 million employees from 13,000 enterprises are
participating in the unemployment insurance plan, with coverage
extending to 85 percent.
</P>
<P>
To date, the province has given out unemployment relief funds
totaling over 40 million yuan, benefitting a total of 280,000
jobless or workers with financial problems.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, through job-transfer training programs, more than
140,000 laid-offs and unemployed people in the province have been
re-employed.
</P>
<P>
Great headway has also been made in the insurance reform for
job injuries, combining production safety measures,
preventive steps against accidents, and prevention and treatment
of occupational diseases.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the child-bearing insurance program now covers 10
counties and 380 enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
