PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Sergi Bruguera, the last-surviving
seed in the men's singles, reached a semi-final showdown with
Australia's Patrick Rafter at the French Open by defeated Moroccan
newcomer Hicham Arazi in four sets on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Rafter didn't drop a set as he destroyed Bruguera's
20-year-old compatriot Galo Blanco with a spectacular display of
serve-and-volley tennis at 6-3, 7-6 (7-3) and 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Bruguera, seeded 16th, defeated 55th-ranked Arazi 4-6, 6-3, 6-2
and 6-2 in two hours 16 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Bruguera will meet Rafter on Friday. 
</P>
