<HEADLINE> Chilean Wine Exports Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Chile's wine exports increased
57.8 percent in value and 29 percent in volume during the first
four months of this year as compared with the same period last
year, said wine producers.
</P>
<P>
Foreign sales reached 108.7 million U.S. dollars during that
period, according to local press today quoting the Association of
Exporters of Fine Wines.
</P>
<P>
Europe remains the biggest market with 46 million dollars or
42.3 percent of sales followed by North America with 41 million
dollars and Asia with 8 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
China, Singapore, South Korea, Hong Kong and Taiwan are five
of the markets where more Chilean wine was sold last year.
France, Brazil, Argentina, Switzerland and Venezuela also
increased their purchases of this product. 
</P>
