<HEADLINE> Extended Airport Lounge Put Into Use in South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A newly-extended lounge has
just opened at Shantou Airport, one of the country's busiest
airports in south China's Guangdong Province,
</P>
<P>
The rebuilt lounge for domestic flights, covering an area of
6,426 square meters, can accommodate up to three million of
passengers per year.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the flow of passengers and cargo in the airport hit an
all-time high of 1.96 million and 27,900 tons, ranking 13th and the
15th, respectively, among the country's 139 airports.
</P>
<P>
Shantou Airport now has flights available to 39 cities at home
and five cities abroad.
</P>
<P>
Airport officials said that the renovated lounge was included
in the airport's overall reconstruction work, which started last
October and is scheduled to be finished in September at a cost of
108 million yuan.  
</P>
